<br>
I've been a casual EQ player since April of 1999. In all that time I've been playing meele classes and have a 53rd level Ranger as my main.<br>
<br>
Just recently I was getting tired of my Ranger chasing after Griffon butts in JPF so I decided to try something completly different and start a Wizard. (For those Phineas Fingers fans, I've always liked the character &quot;Boardflak The Bolt Lobber&quot; <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br>
<br>
In any event, I've soloed my Wizard up to 16th level. My only problem is that my only experience with a wizard grouping is what I've observed from a melee classes point of view. I've been looking for a guide or forum thread that spells out in detail what a grouped wizard should do, but I haven't found one.<br>
<br>
Any help here would be greatly appreciated.<br>
<br>
Amrap<br>
16th level Wizard<br>
Mith-Marr  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bistanti>bistanti</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/19/03 5:22 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> reply</span><hr size=1> depends on ur level.  i have a 63 wiz on the rathe, so i really dont remember too too much around lvl 16.  u nuke obviously but at that lvl u cant compete with twinked out melee's.  even semi twinked melee's way outdamage us at that lvl.<br>
<br>
at 29 u get a snare, so u can play back up snare if no ranger or druid.  think at 27 wizzies get there first evac spell,  that's always nice.<br>
<br>
also at around lvl 29 i started soloin, and quaded all the way through 59.  rarely grouped unless i was bored.<br>
<br>
anyways, at my level in a group, i nuke obviously.  u get half second evacs with aa like druids.  can TL peeps after group falls.  can snare, can root for crowd control if no chanter.  also wizards are nice to have if u need ALOT of dps REAL fast.  usually in a group i dont drop below 70m, thats around 3 nukes and a snare maybe each pull.  if we get 2 or 3 pulls, or say if the healer is lom, a wizard can dump alot of that mana and put out insane damage in a short amount of time.<br>
<br>
well that's my view. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=swipey>Swipey</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 420<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/22/03 5:33 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: reply</span><hr size=1> The first evac is lesser evac (to safepoint) at level 18.<br>
<br>
In groups the wizzie nukes is about it.  you can also do some minor crowd control with your root if your puller brings more than one (why let the second one beat your tank while everyone kills teh first one, eh?)<br>
<br>
Anyway, your life changes at 19.  thats when you get nexus gate. (bind near your hunting ground, gate to nexus, get KEI, gate to bind... go wild) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=erithiel>Erithiel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/27/03 6:10 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: reply</span><hr size=1> Quadding is the fastest way to level, imo, but often grouping is more fun. Every once in awhile you get in a good group with peeps who know what they are doing. This is great, but it doesnt change your role: to nuke<br>
<br>
The tricky part is when to nuke. In groups with high dps, nuking early may be important, if you can affort to nuke each mob more than once. With KEI this should be true most of the time. Learning how early you can start is hard, and when you fail and get aggro, the cleric will have to save your ass with small spotheals, which is very mana inefficient. If you nuke to late, your may end up interrupting your own nukes because they would hit too late.<br>
<br>
When you gat your second stunn spell, at 44 iirc, you can help the cleric by stunning in stead of nuking. Do this in groups with many melees.<br>
<br>
You can also use your spells to disrupt npc casters. A few of them have stunn 0.0 sec, and a relatively short casting time. This is more useful if you face a single strong opponent.<br>
<br>
Good luck<br>
<br>
Erithiel<br>
Wiz 51, Vazaelle <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=enochsire>Enochsire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/6/03 2:31 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> grouping</span><hr size=1> i enjoy a good group, and the key is knowing when to nuke.  now don't laugh, but if you're in a group with a decent tank, when the mob is pulled, go up and melee, yep, i said melee.  the tank has aggro, so you work on your skills, this has saved my butt, being able to melee when oom and medding then a goblin comes up...heh<br>
anyway, melee till mob is at or less than 80% hp, then either back off and nuke, or depending on the group, stand your ground and nuke.  it took some time to get the hang of, the melee w/out aggro, then nuking at the just the right time to drop the mob from berserk mode to run, and when he runs, go melee, unless it's rooted, he'll hit ya if he's rooted.   <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Enochsire Chaosweaver lvl 32<br>
Faithful Dragons of Flight<br>
7th Hammer <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=solanari>Solanari</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/11/03 12:59 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: grouping</span><hr size=1> Everything on these responses i have agreed with.  One thing I have not seen that I highly recomend.<br>
<br>
Tishanis Clash and Markars Clash <br>
<br>
Two stuns spells.  Tishani's Clash has saved my bacon countless times! It is an8 second stun and Markars is an 8 to 12 second stun I do believe.  You can, if you time it right and know that aggro tendancies of the mob chain stun the target.  Saving Cleric (or healer) mana.<br>
<br>
It is up to you - gives you somthing to do besides sit and wait till 75pct to start your attacks....*shrug*<br>
<br>
Just be careful not to stun toearly, cause stunning tick's mobs off somthing fierce.   <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.attbi.com/~trentmking/ss/tkwizard01.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><!--EZCODE CODE START--><pre>       Solanari Lyetbringer<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Commander of The Phoenix Legion<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Wizard of 52 Seasons</pre><!--EZCODE CODE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=erdanliev>Erdanliev</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/21/03 12:53 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Basic wizard guides</span><hr size=1> Actually, there are a couple sections in the library area that tell you exactly what you're looking for, as far as how to play a new wizard.  Under the &quot;Knowledge for Apprentice Wizards&quot; block, there's a section that talks about skills, called &quot;Wizard Basics&quot;.  You want to read the sections &quot;Mana Usage&quot;, &quot;Play Guide&quot;, and &quot;Area Effect Spells&quot; to start with.  After that, feel free to ask questions of a local 20 to 40 wizard, (I recommend that level range because they'd be more familiar with the lower level spells than the high level players).  Good luck!<br>
<br>
